snippet.title: Amber Heard, Johnny Depp attended Thanksgiving party with Marilyn Manson | Page Six Celebrity News
snippet.description:
Amber Heard and Johnny Depp’s family celebrated with Marilyn Manson at a Thanksgiving bash, new footage that emerged in court Wednesday shows — as the actress was accused of “making up” claims that Depp violently assaulted her.

The British court presiding over Depp’s blockbuster libel trial against The Sun was played footage from the Nov. 26, 2015, gathering in Los Angeles, where Manson jokes with Depp’s son, Jack, 18, about a “monster” being in the room while Heard’s father, David, flicks a scarf around.

“He’s a monster,” the male voice, identified by Heard as Manson, says off-camera.

Heard’s father then takes off chasing Jack around the party, where the actress and Depp were also joined by friend Raquel Pennington.

#AmberHeard #JohnnyDepp
